ixed) [http://jam.canoe.ca/Music/Artists/S/Snow/AlbumReviews/2000/10/20/771895.html link] }}\n\n'''''Mind on the Moon''''' is an album by [[Canada|Canadian]] [[reggae]] musician [[Snow (musician)|Snow]], released in 2000. Despite being his fifth album, this was the first disc since his 1993 debut ''[[12 Inches of Snow]]'' that Snow returned to the pop charts and received mainstream airplay on both [[radio]] and [[television]].\n\nThe initial single \"Everybody Wants To Be Like You\" received the most radio play, but it was the second single, \"The Plumb Song\", that was on the heavier rotation on [[MuchMusic]]. This was likely due to the music video which featured Snow play every role, with the different characters having interactions with each other. \"Joke Thing\" and \"Nothin' On Me\" were less successful singles off the album.\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Tracklist\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n\n| title1       = Joke Thing\n| writer1      = {{hlist|Darrin O'Brien|Robbie Patterson|Mark Jackson}}\n| extra1       = {{hlist|O'Brien|Patterson|Justin Gray}}\n| length1      = 3:25\n| title2       = [[Everybody Wants to Be Like You]]\n| writer2      = {{hlist|O'Brien|Patterson|Glenn Marais|Shawn Moltke}}\n| extra2       = Michael Tucker\n| length2      = 3:20\n| title3       = Plumb Song\n| writer3      = {{hlist|O'Brien|Glenn Rosenstein|Moltke}}\n| extra3       = Gray\n| length3      = 3:46\n| title4       = Nothin' On Me\n| writer4      = {{hlist|O'Brien|Patterson|Tucker|Dave Greenberg}}\n| extra4       = {{hlist|Tucker|Greenberg}}\n| length4      = 3:38\n| title5       = Scrub Off\n| writer5      = {{hlist|O'Brien|Gray|Patterson}}\n| extra5       = Gray\n| length5      = 3:25\n| title6       = Everything's Fine\n| writer6      = {{hlist|[[Greig Nori]]|[[Deryck Whibley]]|O'Brien|[[Gerry Goffin]]|[[Michael Masser]]}}\n| extra6       = Nori\n| length6      = 3:57\n| title7       = Little Did They Know\n| writer7      = {{hlist|Simon Head|O'Brien|Moltke}}\n| extra7       = 