{"title_page": "Liu Cuiqing", "text_new": "{{short description|Chinese Paralympic athlete}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Liu (surname)|Liu]]}}\n{{confused|text=[[Li Cuiqing]], a Chinese Paralympic athlete competing in shot put}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| headercolor      = \n| name             = \n| image            = Liu Cuiqing and Xu Donglin Rio2016.jpg\n| image_size       = \n| caption          = Liu and Xu run 100 m at the 2016 Paralympics\n| birth_name       = \n| fullname         = \n| nickname         = \n| nationality      = \n| residence        = \n| birth_date       = {{nowrap|{{birth date and age|1991|10|28}}}}\n| birth_place      = \n| death_date       = \n| death_place      = \n| height           = \n| weight           = \n| website          = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} !-->\n| country          = \n| sport            = Athletics\n| event            = Sprint, [[long jump]]\n| collegeteam      = \n| club             = \n| team             = \n| turnedpro        = \n| disability_class = [[B1 (classification)|T11]]\n| coach            = \n| retired          = \n| coaching         = \n| worlds           = \n| regionals        = \n| nationals        = \n| olympics         = \n| paralympics      = \n| highestranking   = \n| pb               = \n| medaltemplates   = \n{{MedalSport | Women's [[para athletics]] }}\n{{MedalCountry | {{CHN}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Athletics at the Summer Paralympics|Paralympic Games]] }}\n{{MedalGold | [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Paralympics|2016 Rio de Janeiro]] | [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's 4 \u00d7 100 metres relay|4 \u00d7 100 m \u2013 T11-13]]}}\n{{MedalSilver | [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Paralympics|2016 Rio de Janeiro]] | [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's 200 metres T11|200 m \u2013 T11]] }}\n{{MedalBronze | [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Paralympics|2016 Rio de Janeiro]] | [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's 100 metres T11|100 m \u2013 T11]] }}\n}}\n\n'''Liu Cuiqing''' (born October 28, 1991) is a [[China|Chinese]] para-[[track and field]] athlete who competed at the [[2016 Summer Paralympics]] in the [[B1 (classification)|T11/F11]] [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's 100 metres T11|100 metres]], [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's 200 metres T11|200 metres]], [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's 400 metres T11|400 metres]] and [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's long jump T11|long jump]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.paralympic.org/cuiqing-liu|title=Cuiqing Liu \u2013 IPC Athletics {{!}} Paralympic Athlete Profile|website=www.paralympic.org|access-date=2016-09-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://results.paralympics.channel4.com/paralympic/athletes/athlete/LIU-Cuiqing-1233816/index.html?intcmp=ev-standing|title=Paralympics \u2013 Channel 4|last=C4Paralympics|website=results.paralympics.channel4.com|access-date=2016-09-11}}</ref> She bronze medaled in the 100 metres with a time of 11.99 seconds.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://results.paralympics.channel4.com/paralympic/track-field/event/women-100m-t11/phase=atw111100/index.html|title=Paralympics \u2013 Channel 4 \u2013 Athletics \u2013 Women's 100m \u2013 T11|last=C4Paralympics|website=results.paralympics.channel4.com|access-date=2016-09-11}}</ref> She runs with guide Xu Donglin.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[China at the 2016 Summer Paralympics]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Liu Cuiqing}}\n* {{IPC athlete|id=cuiqing-liu|old_id=966791}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Liu, Cuiqing}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Paralympic competitors for China]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2016 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Paralympic bronze medalists for China]]\n[[Category:Paralympic silver medalists for China]]\n[[Category:Paralympic gold medalists for China]]\n[[Category:Medalist